annoyance-filter
------------------------------------------

Adaptive Bayesian Junk Mail Filter

Program sifts mail you wish to read from junk arriving in your
mailbox by an adaptive process which gives priority to mail you're
interested in reading, and evolves to block cleverly disguised junk mail.

Install notes:

  Each user must create directory ~/.annoyance-filter and file
  dict.bin from his spam/ham collection. See manual page and
  See usr/share/doc/annoyance-filter-*/INSTALL for more information.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin
  libgcc1
  libstdc++6

Build requirements:
  cygwin

